{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1774014113,"nonce":"2wmQ+3W7RphiZXp45RF5nCK+Rk8=","title":"fix: nil guard for orphaned line_item in item history view","message":"On production, GET /artikel/29 returns a 500 error:\n\n```\nActionView::Template::Error: undefined method 'lending' for nil\n  app/views/parent_items/_item_history.html.erb:9\n```\n\nAn ItemHistory record references a line_item_id whose LineItem either doesn't exist or whose lending association is nil. This is a data integrity issue from v1 (MySQL had no FK constraints).\n\nOnly affects /artikel/29 on production. Other items work fine.\n\nFix: add a nil guard in the view partial (`_item_history.html.erb:9`) so missing associations don't crash the page.","files":null}]}